==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forger
<hw>For"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>forgeur</ets> metal worker, L. <ets>fabricator</ets> artificer. See
<er>Forge</er>, <pos>n. & v. t.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Fabricator</er>.]</ety> <def>One who forges, makes, of forms; a
fabricator; a falsifier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Especially: One guilty of forgery; one who makes or
issues a counterfeit document.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forgery</ent>⟦br⟧
